<NOTE>Post Office to Issue First Picture Postal Card</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. Postal Service will sell picture
postal cards for the first time.
   The two official government picture postal cards will feature
the White House and the Jefferson Memorial.
   The White House card will go on sale Nov. 30 and the Jefferson
Memorial card Dec. 2, both being issued in Washington. The cards
will sell for 50 cents apiece, which includes 15-cents postage.
   The government has sold plain postal cards for years, and
recently many have carried colorful commemorative designs in the
corner.
