<FIRST>r a PM-PornConviction     10-24 0243</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Porn Conviction,0250</SECOND>
<HEAD>Video Distributor Lands Jail for Porn Tapes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A film distributor was sentenced to one year
in prison for marketing videos featuring porn actress Traci Lords
when she was in her teens.
   Rubin Gottesman, 56, of Woodland Hills, pleaded for leniency
before receiving the prison term Monday.
   ``My life has been probably the worst it's ever been the last
three years,'' he told U.S. District Judge David V. Kenyon.
``Please don't send me to jail.''
   But Kenyon said Gottesman clearly had opted for profit over
restraint by distributing the videos.
   Gottesman, the judge said, was too enamored of ``the almighty
dollar'' and lacked ``the fiber or the character to say, `I won't
be involved in that kind of thing. I will not participate in making
that kind of thing happen.'''
   Kenyon also imposed a $100,000 fine on Gottesman's company,
X-Citement Video Inc., and a $650,000 suspended fine.
   Kenyon ruled in June that Gottesman knew Miss Lords was still a
minor when she appeared in the films ``Lust in the Fast Lane,''
``Sex Shoot'' and ``Screaming Desire.''
   Miss Lords, born May 7, 1968, allegedly had used false
identification to get work in sex films beginning in 1984. She
appeared in dozens of movies before she was 18.
   Gottesman's attorney, Stanley Fleischman, argued at trial that
the child pornography law under which his client was convicted was
unconstitutional. ``We will win, in my opinion, on appeal,'' he
said.
</TEXT>
