   The Who, The Four Tops, The Platters, Bobby
Darin and Hank Ballard have been selected to enter the Rock and
Roll Hall of Fame, the Daily News reported today.
   Joining those rock notables, in the forefathers category, will
be Louis Armstrong and Ma Rainey, the newspaper said.
