<HEAD>Mosbacher Announces for Lieutenant Governor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Houston oil executive Rob Mosbacher
announced his candidacy Tuesday as a Republican candidate for
lieutenant governor, joining two Democrats in that race for 1990.
   Mosbacher, 38, is president of Mosbacher Energy Co., an
independent oil and gas exploration and production firm with 110
employees. He is a former top aide to former U.S. Sen. Howard
Baker, R-Tenn.
   His father, Robert A. Mosbacher, is U.S. commerce secretary.
   Democrats in the race to succeed Lt. Gov. Bill Hobby, who is not
seeking re-election, are state Comptroller Bob Bullock and state
Sen. Chet Edwards of Duncanville. Hobby has been lieutenant
governor since 1973.
   Mosbacher pledged that if he is elected, he would leave office
after two terms, or eight years.
