<HEAD>Five Reported Killed In Bubonic Plague Outbreak</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GABORONE, Botswana (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An outbreak of bubonic plague has
killed five people in central Botswana, the Health Ministry said
Tuesday.
   The ministry said 19 other people had contracted the disease in
the Boteti district in the past two weeks, but the outbreak
appeared to be subsiding.
   Health workers were trying to kill rodents and fleas that might
be carriers of the bacterium.
   One primary school near the town of Orapa had been closed after
two pupils there died of the disease, the ministry said.
