<FIRST>r i AM-Soviet-Parliament     10-24 0121</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Soviet-Parliament,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Glance at Structure of Soviet Parliament</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Soviet-Election</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The two-level Soviet parliament:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   CONGRESS OF PEOPLE'S DEPUTIES _ The 2,250-member Congress is
legally the highest organ of state power. It elects the smaller
working legislature called the Supreme Soviet from among its
members. One-third of the deputies are elected by social
organizations and two-thirds by geographic district. It must
approve the budget and any amendments to the constitution. It also
elects the president.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   SUPREME SOVIET _ The 542-member Supreme Soviet is the first
standing legislature in Soviet history. It has the power to pass
laws and approve top government appointments. It has two chambers,
the Council of Nationalities and the Council of the Union.
</TEXT>
