<HEAD>INS Commissioner Approved</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Senate Tuesday night confirmed Gene McNary
as head of the Immigration and Naturalization Service.
   The action came on a voice vote without debate or dissent.
   McNary, 53, a former prosecutor and unsuccessful Republican
candidate for governor of Missouri, has been chief excecutive of
St. Louis County since 1974.
   He succeeds Alan C. Nelson as INS commissioner.
</TEXT>
