<HEAD>Dollar Down, Gold Up in Quiet Markets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar declined against key currencies in
European trading this morning, while the market waited for release
of new economic data.
   Gold was higher in lackluster trading.
   Markets were quiet while waiting for Washington to release
September data on durable goods.
   In slow trading in Tokyo, the dollar closed at 142.10 yen, down
0.30 yen from Monday's close. Later in London, the dollar traded at
141.95 yen.
   Other dollar rates at midmorning, compared with late Monday's
rates, included: 1.8454 West German marks, down from 1.8550; 1.6170
