   In London, it cost $1.5990 to buy one pound, compared with
$1.5945 late Monday.
   London's major gold dealers fixed a recommended price of $366.40
per troy ounce at mid morning today, up from $365.75 late Monday.
   In Zurich, the bid price was $366.40, compared with $366.00 late
Monday.
   Gold in Hong Kong rose 37 cents an ounce on Tuesday to close at
$366.91 per troy ounce.
   Silver was quoted in London at a bid price of $5.10 a troy
ounce, up from Monday's $5.09.
