<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Tenneco     10-24 0261</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Tenneco,0270</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tenneco Posts Higher Third-Quarter Income</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tenneco Inc. said its third-quarter profit soared
more than tenfold from a year ago.
   For the three months ended Sept. 30, Tenneco earned $90 million,
or 68 cents per share, on revenue of $3.2 billion. That compared
with a profit of of $7 million, or 2 cents per share, and $3
billion in revenue in 1988.
   Tenneco Chairman James L. Ketelson said the gain came because of
strong results in the agricultural and construction equipment units
and improvements in the natural gas pipeline business.
   For the first nine months of 1989, the company had earnings of
$379 million, or $2.88 per share, compared with earnings of $224
million, or $1.39 a share, the same time last year.
   Revenue rose to $10.19 billion from $9.63 billion.
   The company's natural gas pipeline division had an operating
income of $56 million for the third quarter, compared to $45
million in 1988, while the J I Case division had an operating
income of $46 million vs. a $20 million loss in 1988.
   Tenneco Automotive recorded income of $69 million for the
quarter, up $10 million from 1988, and Newport News Shipbuilding
had an income of $37 million for the quarter, down from the $43
million posted last year.
   The company's Packaging Corp. of America reported income of $44
million, compared to $60 million for the corresponding 1988 period
and Albright &amp; Wilson and Tenneco Minerals recorded an operating
income of $20 million for the quarter, down $1 million for the same
period in 1988.
